    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Strongly adhesive, waterproof cloth tape, usually coated on the cloth side with a thermoplastic such as polyethylene. Most often used for sealing ducts against moisture and air leaks, but also used for more general purposes. The 3-ply product was initially composed of a plastic cellulose nitrate laminated cotton strips coated with a rubber-based adhesive. Within a short time, the plastic coating was switched to polyethylene to increase water resistance.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para una cinta de tela fuertemente adhesiva, habitualmente revestida en el lado de la tela con un termoplástico como polietileno y diseñada para sellar conductos contra la humedad y las filtraciones de aire, pero también utilizada para propósitos generales.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor sterk hechtende tape op textielbasis, meestal aan de textielzijde voorzien van een thermoplast zoals polyethyleen. Ontworpen voor het waterdicht maken van leidingen ter bescherming tegen vocht en luchtlekken, maar ook gebruikt voor meer algemene doeleinden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱黏性很強的防水布膠帶，布料面通常覆塗聚乙烯之類的熱塑性塑膠。大多用於密封導管以防受潮或漏氣，但也可用於較一般性的用途。這個三層產品最早是以在棉布外加壓一層硝化纖維素塑料，再上一層含有橡膠粘接劑。產品問世不久之後便以聚乙烯取代塑膠料塗層，以便提高防水度。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
